<HEADLINE>
MAINLAND AFFAIRS COUNCIL CHIEF TO VISIT U.S. THINK TANKS
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  Aug.  5  (CNA) (By Bear Lee)
</P>
<P>
Chairwoman Tsai Ing-wen of the Mainand Affairs Council (MAC) is
scheduled to leave Saturday for the United States to visit established
think tanks there.
</P>
<P>
Chen Chung-hung, director of the MAC's Liaison Department said that
Tsai will first arrive in Los Angels where she will give a speech
using a "Tom Hall" forum on President Chen Shui-bian's
administration's policy regarding mainland China.
</P>
<P>
The Tom Hall format is one of the most important and influential
public forums in the United States. Former U.S. President George Bush,
former British Prime Minister Margret Thatcher and former United
Nation Secretary-General Kofi Annan gave speeches using the format. 0
</P>
<P>
Tsai will then fly to New York and Washington D.C. where she will meet
members of influential U.S. think tanks, including the Center for
Strategic and International Studies, the American Enterprise Institute
and the Council on Foreign Relations.
</P>
<P>
Tsai will return to Taiwan on Aug. 17.
</P>
